◆ prepareWriteRow()

def prepareWriteRow ( row  )

Prepares a row that exist already to be updated at the next call of writeRow()

This method has to be called in case some columns should be updated in a row that was already written. Important: This method has to be called before any value of the columns is updated, for example with the secCellX methods of a fits_data_model class. Once this method is called then the next calls of writeRow() will not add a new row to the end of the table but will update the row, defined by the parameter row. Following calls of writeRow() will write to the next row, independent if it exist already or not. That means this function has to be called only once with prepareWriteRow(1) to update all rows with consecutive calls of writeRow()

Parameters
row[int] At the next call of writeRow() the row will be updated instead of creating a new row. If row is larger than the last row a new row will be added at the next call of writeRow(). Note: first row = 1!

◆ readRow()

def readRow ( row  = 0)

Reads the next row from the FITS table. The cells in this row are then accessible through the getCell...() methods.

Parameters
row[int] Reads data of row number row. First row in the table is row == 1. If row is set to 0 (the default value) data of the next row are read.
Returns
false if the "read pointer" points behind the end of the table and no further row can be read. (Or in case of an error) true if a row could be read

◆ setReadRow()

def setReadRow ( row  )

Sets the row of the FITS table that will be read with the next call of readRow(0), or the next time the table is iterated over (readRow() is called internally by the iterator).

Parameters
row[int] Row number of next row to be read by readRow(0). First row in the table is row == 1.
Returns
false if the row is == 0 or if the number of rows in the table is less than row. true if the row number row can be read.

◆ writeCurrentStatus()

def writeCurrentStatus ( filename  )

Writes the current status into a new FITS file.

This method should be used only for debugging purpose. Only the FITS table or the FITS image can be copied into the new FITS file. The status of the header keywords is not defined.

A FITS table in the saved FITS file may have more rows as already created in this source table. The values in the additional rows are random.

A FITS image will be copied into the primary array of the new FITS file.

Parameters
filenameof the file with the copied data. The file must not exist before calling this method.
Exceptions
runtime_errorif the new file cannot be created or when the write operation fails.

◆ writeRow()

def writeRow ( )

Creates a new row at the end of the table and fills it with the values that have been assigned through the setCell...() methods.
